com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle

Interface Handle

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CacheSessionHandle, ContextHandle, FlowHandle, MessageDispatchTargetHandle, MessageHandle, NativeDestinationHandle, SessionHandle, TransactedSessionHandle

    public interface Handle
    Abstraction of a native object.

    A Handle represents a binding of an API layer concept to its underlying native object. A Handle instance is created by calling one of the of Solclient.Allocator new methods

    A Handle instance has the following characteristics:

    • A Handle instance is not bound to a native object when it's initially created. Calling Handle.isBound() will return false
    • A Handle instance becomes bound after it's passed in to one of the create methods (for example Solclient.createContextForHandle())
    • Calling Handle.destroy() will destroy the native object and render the Handle reference unbound. At this point, the Handle instance can be re-used.
